40}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 5446, \"to\": 5452}, {\"ngram\": \"a minimum\", \"from\": 5456, \"to\": 5465}, {\"ngram\": \"thecoronaviruspandemic\", \"from\": 5472, \"to\": 5494}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There were alsothosecardboard cots that social media usersdubbed the \\\"anti-sex\\\" beds.And while condoms were handed out to the athletes, the intention was for them to \\\"take them back to their home countries and raise awareness\\\" for HIV and AIDS, organizers toldReuters.While the cardboard beds are back for the 2024 Paris Olympics, there is not the same level of social distancing protocols.\", \"from\": 5497, \"to\": 5887, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"alsothosecardboard cots\", \"from\": 5508, \"to\": 5531}, {\"ngram\": \"social media\", \"from\": 5537, \"to\": 5549}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"anti-sex\\\" beds\", \"from\": 5562, \"to\": 5581}, {\"ngram\": \"condoms\", \"from\": 5592, \"to\": 5599}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 5619, \"to\": 5631}, {\"ngram\": \"the intention\", \"from\": 5633, \"to\": 5646}, {\"ngram\": \"their home countries\", \"from\": 5682, \"to\": 5702}, {\"ngram\": \"awareness\", \"from\": 5713, \"to\": 5722}, {\"ngram\": \"HIV\", \"from\": 5728, \"to\": 5731}, {\"ngram\": \"AIDS\", \"from\": 5736, \"to\": 5740}, {\"ngram\": \"organizers\", \"from\": 5742, \"to\": 5752}, {\"ngram\": \"toldReuters\", \"from\": 5753, \"to\": 5764}, {\"ngram\": \"the cardboard beds\", \"from\": 5771, \"to\": 5789}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 5803, \"to\": 5826}, {\"ngram\": \"the same level\", \"from\": 5841, \"to\": 5855}, {\"ngram\": \"social distancing protocols\", \"from\": 5859, \"to\": 5886}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And there will be condoms on hand for the approximately 14,250 Olympic Village residents.\", \"from\": 5888, \"to\": 5977, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5951, \"end\": 5966, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1377363279083481e-35, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"condoms\", \"from\": 5906, \"to\": 5913}, {\"ngram\": \"hand\", \"from\": 5917, \"to\": 5921}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are aiming to have 300,000 condoms here at disposal for the athletes in the village,\\\" Michaud told Sky News.\", \"from\": 5977, \"to\": 6089, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6080, \"end\": 6088, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_News\", \"score\": 0.9999999999654392, \"rank\": 3.451394763385292e-11, \"text\": \"Sky News\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_News\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"300,000 condoms\", \"from\": 6000, \"to\": 6015}, {\"ngram\": \"disposal\", \"from\": 6024, \"to\": 6032}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 6037, \"to\": 6049}, {\"ngram\": \"the village\", \"from\": 6053, \"to\": 6064}, {\"ngram\": \"Michaud\", \"from\": 6067, \"to\": 6074}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's a quantity that makes sure that everybody will have what they are expecting and what they need.\\\"\", \"from\": 6090, \"to\": 6192, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a quantity\", \"from\": 6096, \"to\": 6106}, {\"ngram\": \"everybody\", \"from\": 6128, \"to\": 6137}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Social Media Standards If athletes want to share social media content, they are going to need to follow some #rules.For instance, the International Olympic Committee's guidelines state athletes can share audio and video recordings from the Opening and Closing Ceremonies, Olympic Village, Champions Park, training venues and practice areas.\", \"from\": 6194, \"to\": 6535, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6329, \"end\": 6360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 6467, \"end\": 6482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1377363279083481e-35, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Social Media Standards\", \"from\": 6194, \"to\": 6216}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 6220, \"to\": 6228}, {\"ngram\": \"social media content\", \"from\": 6243, \"to\": 6263}, {\"ngram\": \"some #rules\", \"from\": 6298, \"to\": 6309}, {\"ngram\": \"instance\", \"from\": 6314, \"to\": 6322}, {\"ngram\": \"audio and video recordings\", \"from\": 6398, \"to\": 6424}, {\"ngram\": \"the Opening and Closing Ceremonies\", \"from\": 6430, \"to\": 6464}, {\"ngram\": \"Champions Park\", \"from\": 6483, \"to\": 6497}, {\"ngram\": \"training venues\", \"from\": 6499, \"to\": 6514}, {\"ngram\": \"practice areas\", \"from\": 6519, \"to\": 6533}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The rules also note athletes can post recordings from competition veneus up to an hour before their events begin and after the they have left the \\\"mixed zone/doping control station.\", \"from\": 6536, \"to\": 6717, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The rules\", \"from\": 6536, \"to\": 6545}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 6556, \"to\": 6564}, {\"ngram\": \"recordings\", \"from\": 6574, \"to\": 6584}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 6590, \"to\": 6601}, {\"ngram\": \"an hour\", \"from\": 6615, \"to\": 6622}, {\"ngram\": \"their events\", \"from\": 6630, \"to\": 6642}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"mixed zone/doping control station\", \"from\": 6678, \"to\": 6716}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"However, the guidelines make it clear that these recordings cannot exceed two minutes per post.\", \"from\": 6717, \"to\": 6813, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the guidelines\", \"from\": 6727, \"to\": 6741}, {\"ngram\": \"these recordings\", \"from\": 6761, \"to\": 6777}, {\"ngram\": \"two minutes\", \"from\": 6792, \"to\": 6803}, {\"ngram\": \"post\", \"from\": 6808, \"to\": 6812}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition, the rules state athletes cannot share videos of medal ceremonies or sports competitions (including anthems, coin tosses or celebrations on the field) and that the clips cannot be live.And while photos can be taken at the Games if the Olympians follow the guidelines, the rules explain that pictures and videos cannot be shared if they are commercial, use AI or feature the \\\"medical areas, doping control station or mult-faith centre.\\\"\", \"from\": 6814, \"to\": 7261, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7182, \"end\": 7184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.999999601876959, \"rank\": 3.981231153725155e-07, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"addition\", \"from\": 6817, \"to\": 6825}, {\"ngram\": \"the rules state athletes\", \"from\": 6827, \"to\": 6851}, {\"ngram\": \"videos\", \"from\": 6865, \"to\": 6871}, {\"ngram\": \"medal ceremonies\", \"from\": 6875, \"to\": 6891}, {\"ngram\": \"sports competitions\", \"from\": 6895, \"to\": 6914}, {\"ngram\": \"anthems\", \"from\": 6926, \"to\": 6933}, {\"ngram\": \"coin tosses\", \"from\": 6935, \"to\": 6946}, {\"ngram\": \"celebrations\", \"from\": 6950, \"to\": 6962}, {\"ngram\": \"the field\", \"from\": 6966, \"to\": 6975}, {\"ngram\": \"the clips\", \"from\": 6986, \"to\": 6995}, {\"ngram\": \"photos\", \"from\": 7021, \"to\": 7027}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 7044, \"to\": 7053}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympians\", \"from\": 7057, \"to\": 7070}, {\"ngram\": \"the guidelines\", \"from\": 7078, \"to\": 7092}, {\"ngram\": \"the rules\", \"from\": 7094, \"to\": 7103}, {\"ngram\": \"pictures\", \"from\": 7117, \"to\": 7125}, {\"ngram\": \"videos\", \"from\": 7130, \"to\": 7136}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"medical areas\", \"from\": 7196, \"to\": 7214}, {\"ngram\": \"doping control station\", \"from\": 7216, \"to\": 7238}, {\"ngram\": \"mult-faith centre\", \"from\": 7242, \"to\": 7259}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Barring Plastic Bottles Trying to help the planet?\", \"from\": 7263, \"to\": 7314, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Plastic Bottles\", \"from\": 7271, \"to\": 7286}, {\"ngram\": \"the planet\", \"from\": 7302, \"to\": 7312}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now that move deserves a gold medal.Paris is banning single-use plastics during the 2024 Olympics, including at festival sites, competition locations and the Marathon Pour Tous.According to the city's tourism website, reusable, non-glass water bottles will be allowed at festival and competition sites and attendees will be permitted to bring their own containers, bowls or cups for eating and drinking.\", \"from\": 7315, \"to\": 7718, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a gold medal\", \"from\": 7338, \"to\": 7350}, {\"ngram\": \"Paris\", \"from\": 7351, \"to\": 7356}, {\"ngram\": \"single-use plastics\", \"from\": 7368, \"to\": 7387}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Olympics\", \"from\": 7395, \"to\": 7412}, {\"ngram\": \"festival sites\", \"from\": 7427, \"to\": 7441}, {\"ngram\": \"competition locations\", \"from\": 7443, \"to\": 7464}, {\"ngram\": \"the Marathon Pour Tous\", \"from\": 7469, \"to\": 7491}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's tourism website\", \"from\": 7505, \"to\": 7531}, {\"ngram\": \"reusable, non-glass water bottles\", \"from\": 7533, \"to\": 7566}, {\"ngram\": \"festival and competition sites\", \"from\": 7586, \"to\": 7616}, {\"ngram\": \"attendees\", \"from\": 7621, \"to\": 7630}, {\"ngram\": \"their own containers\", \"from\": 7658, 